# Centralized Runtime Strings

- Do not embed runtime-facing string literals or templates directly inside normal class methods.
- Centralize error codes, error messages, validation messages, problem titles/details, and exception text in dedicated catalog or resource-style classes.
- Reference the centralized catalog from handlers, services, validators, infrastructure helpers, and configuration code.
- Prefer small, concern-focused catalog classes close to the owning layer instead of a single global dump file.
- It is acceptable for the centralized catalog itself to contain the literal text or formatting template.
- Test assertions may keep explicit expected strings when that improves test clarity and avoids coupling the test to the production catalog.
